<P>
SOME CABLE TV RATES TO RISE IN SUMMER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIM KASH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cable TV costs for some Oxnard and Port Hueneme customers will increase this 
summer by as much as $1.50 per month. 
</P>
<P>
Jones Intercable, which serves about 34,000 people in the two cities, will 
charge $16 for basic cable service beginning July 1, a $1 increase over current 
rates. Remote control cable boxes will cost an additional $3.45, a 50-cent 
increase over current rates, said Linda Merkel, a spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
Jones Intercable plans to use much of the increased revenue to purchase backup 
batteries for its satellite receiving stations, Merkel said. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Lombardi, a management analyst for Oxnard, said that the cities of Port 
Hueneme and Oxnard now do not have the power to regulate cable company rates. 
KIM KASH 
</P>
