<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : $250,000 RAISED IN DRIVE FOR 2 CATHOLIC 
SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parishioners, local businesses and community leaders have raised $250,000 for 
the high school and elementary school affiliated with St. Monica Catholic 
Church in Santa Monica, school officials have announced. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the money, $200,000, will go to St. Monica High School for a 10% 
increase in teachers' salaries and for hiring a counselor, an administrator and 
another teacher at the 51-year-old school, said the principal, Sister Cheryl 
Milner. Teacher salaries now start at $23,000, she said. 
</P>
<P>
