<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
3 MEN CONVICTED OF SELLING COCAINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Ventura County Superior Court jury convicted three men Tuesday of selling 
crack cocaine from a dilapidated house in west Ventura in February. 
</P>
<P>
Alonzo Haynes, 38, was convicted on one count each of maintaining a house for 
illicit narcotics sales and selling crack cocaine. 
</P>
<P>
Duchon Fields, 23, of Ventura was convicted on two counts of selling crack 
cocaine but acquitted on a third count. Dexter Williams, 23, was convicted on 
one count of selling crack cocaine. 
</P>
<P>
All three were being held in the Ventura County Jail pending their sentencing 
hearing, scheduled for July 10. 
</P>
<P>
The men were arrested in a Feb. 26 raid on the house at 948 Olive St. by SWAT 
teams from the Ventura Police Department and the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
During the trial, a police informant testified that she bought small quantities 
of crack at the house from Fields and Haynes on Feb. 13 and from Williams on 
Feb. 14. MACK REED 
</P>
