SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The board of the Escondido Union High School District unanimously approved a 
contract Tuesday to hire a replacement for its much-maligned superintendent, 
John Cooper. 
</P>
<P>
Jane Gawronski, superintendent of the West Covina Union School District, will 
take the helm of the 5,700-student school district July 16, replacing Cooper, 
whom the school board asked to resign late last year after complaints about his 
management style. 
</P>
<P>
Gawronski, whose three-year contract calls for a starting salary of $85,000 a 
year, has been superintendent at West Covina since 1987, bringing the district 
back from the brink of insolvency. 
</P>
<P>
"There are challenges in Escondido, too," Gawronski said. "But the primary 
challenge is a people one, not a fiscal one. Both problems require process 
solutions, because it takes people to provide solutions." 
</P>
<P>
Cooper, who still had one year left on his contract, will vacate his post June 
30. 
</P>
