<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: $4-MILLION NORDHOFF BRIDGE, LINK OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $4-million connector road designed to ease congestion on Nordhoff Street in 
Northridge was opened to traffic Tuesday, city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The nearly half-mile long connector, which includes a bridge over Southern 
Pacific railroad tracks and Limekiln Creek, closes a gap in Nordhoff between 
Tampa and Corbin avenues. 
</P>
<P>
The city has wanted to link Nordhoff into a continuous thoroughfare since 1972, 
but the project was not funded until 1986, when the owners of the Northridge 
Fashion Center agreed to pay $1.5 million of the cost in return for city 
permission to expand the mall. 
</P>
<P>
City officials expect the extention to carry 35,000 vehicles a day. 
</P>
