<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: MOORPARK HIGH TO PLAY CANADIAN SCHOOL IN FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moorpark High has scheduled a football game for Sept. 14 against a team from 
Canada, giving the area two such matchups that weekend. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark will play host to Okotoks High from Alberta, one night before Village 
Christian meets St. Mary's of Calgary at Kennedy High. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark originally was scheduled to play Village Christian that weekend, but 
Coach Mike Plaisance arranged the St. Mary's game and asked Moorpark to release 
his school from its contract. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark Coach Rob Dearborn agreed on the condition that Moorpark find a 
replacement. When Dearborn failed in that endeavor, Plaisance arranged for the 
second Canadian team to head south. 
</P>
<P>
Senior right-handers Robert Ramirez and Jakob Jensen of Highland Hall have been 
selected to the All-Southern Section Small Schools Division first team by a 
panel of sportswriters. 
</P>
<P>
Ramirez (12-3, 1.83 earned-run average, .579 batting average) was selected for 
the second consecutive season. Jensen batted .518 and was 9-1 with an ERA of 
2.85. 
</P>
</TEXT>
