BETTING WITH BOB; 
</P>
<P>
MAN VS. MICROCHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After four days of racing, I'm $30 in the black with my second bankroll. Not 
bad considering what happened to the first one, but not great after my $190 
profit on the first day with the second. 
</P>
<P>
Misery loves company, however, and thank goodness for the computer thus far. 
Perhaps it needs to re-read "DOS Kapital." 
</P>
<P>
For today I'll bet $15 exactas from Mittens And Mink to Rash Decision and Blue 
Sonata. 
</P>
<P>
Bob's Sunday Bankroll $2,070 
</P>
<P>
Sunday's Loss $40 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $2,030 
</P>
<P>
The computer seems to distrust the main track at Hollywood Park. It is sticking 
with the turf for its bets today: a $40 exacta of Belle Poitrine to Bragora, a 
$20 exacta reversing the two and a $10 exacta box of Belle Poitrine, Bragora 
and Imperial Star in the ninth race. 
</P>
