MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
From Breathless to Blondie: Based on the runaway success of "Batman" and the 
anticipated success of "Dick Tracy," Walt Disney Pictures is preparing a 
feature musical film based on the comic strip "Blondie." 
</P>
<P>
Alfred Uhry, who won an Oscar for the screenplay adaptation of "Driving Miss 
Daisy," will do the screenplay. The film is tentatively scheduled to start 
production next spring for a 1992 summer release. Disney is in active 
discussions with Howard Ashman and Alan Menken, who won Oscars for their work 
on "The Little Mermaid," to write the score. Dean Young, who writes the 
nationally syndicated comic strip seen in some 2,000 newspapers, is set to be 
executive producer. BETH KLEID 
