<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Studios Postpone Fin/Syn Talks: Hollywood studios asked the television networks 
with which they are negotiating to postpone the final round of their talks on 
financial interest and syndication rules. 
</P>
<P>
The Federal Communications Commission has set Thursday as the deadline for the 
sides to reach agreement. The networks and studios were supposed to meet 
Tuesday at Warner Bros. in Burbank, but Jack Valenti, president of the Motion 
Picture Assn. of America, said the studios needed more time to prepare their 
90-page filing with the FCC. The studios are expected to argue against the 
networks being allowed to enter the lucrative TV re-run business. Final 
negotiations are scheduled for 9 a.m. today. Chances of a settlement appear 
remote. 
</P>
