<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : MAN PLEADS NOT GUILTY IN ATTACK ON 
POLICEWOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Highland Park man pleaded not guilty Tuesday to assault and robbery charges 
in the shooting of a Los Angeles police officer who was critically wounded 
during a gun battle in which the defendant's companion was killed. 
</P>
<P>
Arvin Peter Mani, 20, was arraigned in Newhall Municipal Court in Santa 
Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Alan S. Rosenfield set bail at $1 million and scheduled a preliminary 
hearing for June 21. 
</P>
<P>
Two other suspects, girls 13 and 14, were to be arraigned today. They are to be 
charged -- as Mani was Tuesday -- with conspiracy to commit robbery, attempted 
robbery, assault with a deadly weapon and attempted grand theft with a firearm, 
prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
Stacy Lim, the 27-year-old policewoman, remained in guarded condition at Henry 
Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia. 
</P>
