METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : ROBBER SURRENDERS AFTER A 45-MINUTE STANDOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man disarmed a security guard at a Westlake check cashing store Tuesday, then 
blasted away futilely with the guard's gun at a vault lock as employees hid 
behind bulletproof glass. 
</P>
<P>
The man held police at bay for 45 minutes before giving up, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Eddie Artola, 30, was arrested about 5:45 p.m. at the Nix check cashing 
business in the 1800 block of West 6th Street. 
</P>
<P>
After the guard was robbed of his gun, he managed to run outside and call 
police, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
Police surrounded the store and used a bullhorn to talk the robber into 
surrendering. 
</P>
