<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : 7 ARRESTED AFTER AIDS PROTEST TO SUPERVISORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the latest protest by AIDS activists targeting the Los Angeles County Board 
of Supervisors, seven people were arrested Tuesday for disrupting the board's 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators knelt in a front aisle as supervisors were beginning their 
meeting and, backed by about two dozen supporters, broke into a hymn in which 
they identified themselves as lesbians and gays "who are singing for our 
lives." 
</P>
<P>
Among those arrested were Dave Johnson, AIDS coordinator for the city of Los 
Angeles, and three people dressed as members of the clergy. 
</P>
<P>
Supervisors are debating the 1990-91 budget, which calls for no increases in 
the $60 million for AIDS services allocated last year. AIDS activists are 
demanding at least $9 million more. 
</P>
<P>
The seven protesters were arrested without incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
