<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOUL &amp; EGO: When the $17.6-million Irvine Theatre (F1) opens in October, 
the city will finally have "a soul," says Mayor-elect Sally Anne Sheridan. . . 
. The 750-seat theater will also have a new name -- the Irvine Barclay Theatre 
-- in honor of Richard H. and Marjorie Barclay of Newport Beach, who pledged $1 
million to help complete construction. Barclay, a Southern California 
developer, concedes there is "probably a little ego" in his donation. Mark I. 
Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</TEXT>
