<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
AUTO REPAIR SHOP DESTROYED BY FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An auto repair shop was destroyed Tuesday in an early-morning fire, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
When firefighters arrived at the Hyundai Repair Shop at 1:51 a.m., the 
structure at 9535 Garden Grove Blvd. was "100% involved," Garden Grove Fire 
Information Officer Ellen Covey said. 
</P>
<P>
It took 16 firefighters about 30 minutes to contain the blaze, which caused 
$125,000 in damage to the building and its contents, she said. No one was 
injured in the fire, Covey said. MATT LAIT 
</P>
</TEXT>
