<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACCOUNTANT SLAIN IN APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A tip from a concerned sister led police Tuesday to the body of a 27-year-old 
accountant who was apparently stabbed to death in his apartment, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police Sgt. Glenn Deveney said the victim was identified as Mark Tomasulo, who 
shared an apartment on the 2400 block of Nutwood Avenue with a 19-year-old man 
whose whereabouts were not immediately known. 
</P>
<P>
Deveney said that police received a call shortly after 3 p.m. Tuesday from 
Michelle Fredrickson of Fullerton, who requested that officers check on the 
welfare of her brother because he had not been seen or heard from since 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Police went to the Nutwood address and found Tomasulo's body bearing stab 
wounds, Deveney said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the victim reportedly worked as an accountant for Beckman 
Instruments and had not been at his job for two days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
