</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East German police have arrested one of West Germany's most wanted leftist 
terrorist suspects, the second such arrest of an alleged Red Army Faction 
member in a week, the government-run news agency said today. 
</P>
<P>
ADN said Inge Viett, 46, was arrested late Tuesday in the East German city of 
Magdeburg. 
</P>
<P>
She is accused of taking part in the murder of prominent West Berlin Judge 
Guenter von Drenkmann in 1974 and the kidnaping a year later of West Berlin 
Christian Democratic leader Peter Lorenz. 
</P>
<P>
In recent days, West German wanted posters appeared in Magdeburg, with names 
and pictures of Viett and nine other accused fugitive terrorists, according to 
ADN. 
