</P>
<P>
AN ANNUAL FAREWELL FOR KEILLOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In what has become an annual field trip to Lake Wobegon, Garrison Keillor 
extends an open invitation to radio listeners to "A Prairie Home Companion: The 
4th Annual Farewell Performance." 
</P>
<P>
Produced by Minnesota Public Radio in conjunction with KSUI-FM in Iowa City, 
the show will be broadcast live Saturday from the University of Iowa on 
American Public Radio. 
</P>
<P>
This "4th Annual Farewell" stems from a tradition started on June 13, 1987, 
when Keillor gave his final live performance from the World Theater in St. 
Paul, Minn. Audience response prompted Keillor to return for a "Second 
Farewell" at New York's Radio City Music Hall in June, 1988, and then a third 
in Los Angeles in June, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Joining Keillor are Jean Redpath, a Scottish folk singer; mandolinist and 
fiddler Peter Ostroushko; and singer Greg Brown. 
</P>
