<P>
ERIN FLEMING ARRESTED WITH GUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Erin Fleming, one-time companion of the late comedian Groucho Marx, was 
arrested after walking into a sheriff's station with a loaded .357 Magnum 
revolver in her purse, authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
Fleming, 48, walked into the West Hollywood sheriff's station at 720 N. San 
Vicente Blvd. carrying a large handbag at about 11 p.m. Tuesday, sheriff's 
Deputy Chris Wahla said. 
</P>
<P>
"As she spoke with station deputies, she placed the handbag on the counter," 
Wahla said. "Visible within the handbag was a 2 1/2-inch stainless steel 
revolver which, after inspection, was found to be loaded." 
</P>
<P>
Fleming was arrested on suspicion of carrying a concealed loaded firearm in a 
public place. She was released on her promise to appear in Beverly Hills 
Municipal Court for arraignment July 6. 
</P>
<P>
"A computer check revealed that the handgun was registered to her," Wahla said. 
</P>
<P>
Fleming was a companion to the late comedian Groucho Marx and was a beneficiary 
of his estate. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies would not say why Fleming went to the station. 
</P>
</TEXT>
