<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S.-CZECH MATCH GETS LOW RATINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States' 5-1 loss to Czechoslovakia in its World Cup opener Sunday 
was watched by fewer than 2% of the nation's television viewers. 
</P>
<P>
The match, which began at 8 a.m. PDT, got a 1.8 overnight rating and a 6 share, 
Turner Broadcasting Co. said. 
</P>
<P>
In contrast, Saturday's game between Italy and Austria got a 74 share in Italy, 
the RAI network said. 
</P>
<P>
A rating point is said by A. C.Nielsen Co. to represent 921,000 homes, or 1% of 
the 92.1 million U.S. households that have TV. The share is the percentage of 
television sets that are on at the time. 
</P>
<P>
The World Cup games are on Turner Broadcasting's TNT cable network in the 
United States. 
</P>
<P>
The overnight ratings are based on survey's of the largest U.S. television 
markets. The final national ratings will not be available until the end of the 
week. 
</P>
