<P>
U.S. WORLD CUP TEAM CRITICIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ERBA, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Franz Beckenbauer today criticized U.S. preparations for this year's World Cup 
and dismissed as "pure speculation" suggestions that he might take a job with 
the U.S. Soccer Federation after the tournament ends. 
</P>
<P>
Beckenbauer, who played for the New York Cosmos in the late 1970s, will quit as 
West German team chief at the end of the World Cup after six years in charge. 
</P>
<P>
Beckenbauer had scathing words about the organization of the current U.S. team, 
trounced 5-1 Sunday by Czechoslovakia. 
</P>
<P>
"They'll have to start reorganizing and building up or they will experience the 
same debacle in four years as here." 
</P>
</TEXT>
